\subsection{Generalised rewrite-bridge \texorpdfstring{$\bigsqcup\mathcal U = U$}{} for HModule\texttt{'} (iter-052)}

Iter-051 lands $\Subsingleton\,(\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,(\bigsqcup_i \mathcal U_i))$ on the lattice supremum. The iter-054+ producer for $\IsAffineHModuleVanishing\,k\,C\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)$ on an affine open $U$ instead needs $\Subsingleton\,(\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,U)$ on the open $U$ itself; it picks a basic-open cover $\mathcal U$ of $U$ (with $\bigsqcup\mathcal U = U$ by construction) and rewrites via the equality. Iter-052 factors this rewrite into a thin theorem (mirroring iter-049's $h\,\rhd\,\mathtt{this}$ factoring at universe $u+1$ for $\HModule$), enabling the iter-054+ producer to use cleaner instance-driven synthesis.

