\subsection{Toward the iter-053+ comparison theorem (informal scoping)}

Mathlib has $\mathtt{cechComplexFunctor}$ (\texttt{Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/SheafCohomology/Cech.lean}) but \emph{no} comparison theorem to derived-functor cohomology. The substantive iter-052+ obligation is to construct, for any sheaf $F$ on $C.\mathtt{left}$ and cover $\mathcal U$ with $[\IsCechAcyclicCover\,F\,\mathcal U]$ (\emph{or} a slightly weaker hypothesis), a natural $\LinearEquiv$
\[
  \mathrm{compIso}_n \,:\, \cechCohomology\,C\,F\,\mathcal U\,n \;\equiv_k\; \HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,\big(\bigsqcup_i \mathcal U_i\big), \qquad \forall n.
\]
The standard mathematical decomposition is the Čech-to-derived spectral sequence:
\[
  E_2^{p,q} \;=\; \check H^p\big(\mathcal U,\, \underline{H^q}(F)\big) \;\Longrightarrow\; H^{p+q}\big(\bigsqcup\mathcal U,\, F\big),
\]
which under the acyclicity hypothesis $\check H^q(\mathcal U_{i_0..i_p}, F) = 0$ for $q > 0$ collapses on the $E_2$ page to give $\check H^n \cong H^n$. Mathlib does not have the spectral-sequence machinery in the required form; the project-local construction is therefore expected via the dual chain-level route:
\begin{enumerate}
  \item View the sheafified-Yoneda-free $\Yoneda^{\mathrm{free}}_\bullet \,:\, n \mapsto (\mathtt{presheafToSheaf}).\mathrm{obj}\big((\mathtt{yoneda} \circ \free\,k).\mathrm{obj}\,(\mathcal U_{i_0\cap\cdots\cap i_n})\big)$ as a complex of sheaves whose homology in degree 0 is $(\mathtt{presheafToSheaf}).\mathrm{obj}\big((\mathtt{yoneda} \circ \free\,k).\mathrm{obj}\,(\bigsqcup\mathcal U)\big)$ (sheafification of the Čech sheaf-resolution of the free sheaf on $\bigsqcup\mathcal U$) and whose higher homologies vanish under acyclicity (the substantive computational step).
  \item Apply $\mathrm{Hom}(-, F)$ degree-wise, picking up $\Hom\big(\Yoneda^{\mathrm{free}}_n,\,F\big) \cong \prod_{i_0,\ldots,i_n} F(\mathcal U_{i_0\cap\cdots\cap i_n}) = (\cechCochain)_n$ on the LHS, and $\Hom\big((\mathtt{presheafToSheaf}).\mathrm{obj}\,(\mathtt{yoneda}\circ\free\,k).\mathrm{obj}\,(\bigsqcup\mathcal U),\, F\big) = \HModulePrime\,k\,F\,0\,(\bigsqcup\mathcal U)$ on the RHS at degree 0.
  \item Pass to cohomology and chain to $\Ext^n$ via the augmentation; under acyclicity the comparison is a quasi-iso, and the induced map on $\Ext^n$ gives the comparison.
\end{enumerate}
This decomposes into multiple iterations: (a) iter-052 constructs the Čech sheaf-resolution of the sheafified-Yoneda-free at degree $\geq 1$ (computational; the alternating face complex is exact under acyclicity); (b) iter-053+ chains via $\Ext$ functoriality. An alternative parallel branch is the basic-open cover acyclicity (Koszul-type alternating-sum exactness on localisations) which can proceed in parallel with the comparison construction. Estimate: 4--6 iterations, $\sim 200$--$400$ LOC.

\subsection{Use in Serre finiteness}

The iter-029 lemmas materialise Step 1 (the abstract LES) and Step 2 (the corner-identification simp lemmas) of the iter-028 Serre-finiteness sketch (Section~\ref{sec:scheme_affineCoverMVSquare}); iter-030 materialised Step 2.5 (the toModuleKSheaf specialisation, a routine binding so downstream code paths can reference the LES on the structure sheaf of a curve directly); iter-031 materialised the \emph{source-object} half of Step 3 (the cover-totality identification at the sheaf level); iter-032 materialised the \emph{Ext-transport} half of Step 3 at universe $u+1$ (landing on $\HModule\,k\,F\,n$); iter-033 materialised the parallel \emph{Ext-transport} at universe $u$ (landing on $\Ext_u\,X_2\,F\,n$); iter-034 closed Step 3 by appending the Mathlib gap-fill $\Ext.\mathtt{chgUnivLinearEquiv}$ (universe-bump $\LinearEquiv$ upgrade of Mathlib's bare $\Equiv$ $\Ext.\mathtt{chgUniv}$) and composing iter-033 with it to produce the full bridge $\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,T \equiv_{\Module k} \HModule\,k\,F\,n$ for terminal $T$; iter-035 closed Step 3.5 (the \emph{corner-bridge}) by specialising the iter-034 universal bridge to the $X_4$ corner of an $\AffineCoverMVSquare$ — both an abstract sheaf form (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_X4_linearEquiv}) and a curve specialisation (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_X4_linearEquiv_curve}); iter-036 appended the immediate \emph{finrank corollary} (Theorems~\ref{thm:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_finrank_HModule_eq_HModule_prime_X4} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_finrank_HModule_eq_HModule_prime_X4_curve}) — landing the genus carrier $\mathrm{finrank}_k\,(\HModule\,k\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)\,1)$ on the explicit corner $X_4$ via $\LinearEquiv.\mathtt{finrank\_eq}$; iter-037 appends the parallel \emph{$\Module.\mathtt{Finite}$ transport companion} (Theorems~\ref{thm:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_module_finite_HModule_of_HModule_prime_X4} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_module_finite_HModule_of_HModule_prime_X4_curve}) — the algebraic counterpart of iter-036, transporting finiteness rather than finrank across the corner-bridge, via Mathlib's $\Module.\mathtt{Finite.equiv}$. Iter-038 → iter-046 build the H⁰ Module.Finite ladder (curve specialisations + carrier predicates + Stein input + global-sections evaluation iso + producer chain end-to-end for $\IsHModuleHomFinite\,k\,C\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)$); iter-047 lays foundational parameterised Čech infrastructure; iter-048 appends the Čech-side acyclicity carrier predicate and abstract consumer; iter-049 appends the top-supremum HModule transport (Theorems~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_of_isCechAcyclicCover_top} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_of_isCechAcyclicCover_top_curve}) — the universe $u \to u+1$ bridge that lets iter-053+ ultimately consume iter-048's $\Subsingleton$ on $\HModulePrime$ at the lattice supremum to derive the genus carrier $\Module.\mathtt{Finite}\,k\,(\HModule\,k\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)\,1)$ at universe $u+1$; iter-050 packages the Čech-vs-derived comparison iso as a $\Prop$-valued typeclass $\Scheme.\HasCechToHModuleIso$ with $\Classical.\mathtt{choice}$-based extractor (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_cechToHModuleIso}) and instance-driven \emph{top-supremum} consumers (Theorems~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_of_hasCechToHModuleIso_top} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_of_hasCechToHModuleIso_top_curve}); iter-051 appends the symmetric instance-driven \emph{intermediate-supremum} consumers (Theorems~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_prime_supr_of_hasCechToHModuleIso} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_prime_supr_of_hasCechToHModuleIso_curve}) — landing $\Subsingleton\,(\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,(\bigsqcup\mathcal U))$ at universe $u$; iter-052 (this iteration) appends the generalised rewrite-bridge $\bigsqcup\mathcal U = U$ consumers (Theorems~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_prime_of_hasCechToHModuleIso} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_prime_of_hasCechToHModuleIso_curve}) — landing $\Subsingleton\,(\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,U)$ on an arbitrary open $U$ under the equality hypothesis, the exact form iter-054+ needs to instantiate $\IsAffineHModuleVanishing\,k\,C\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)$ for an affine open via a basic-open cover. The remaining work — Step 4 (the substantive Čech-vs-derived comparison theorem; iter-053+ multi-iteration; Mathlib has $\mathtt{cechComplexFunctor}$ but no comparison theorem; once landed as a theorem, an instance for $\HasCechToHModuleIso$ wraps it via $\langle\langle \mathtt{the\_iso}\rangle\rangle$) and Step 5 (basic-open cover acyclicity producers; iter-053+ computational; Koszul-like alternating-sum complex on localisations is exact) and Step 6 (assembling the genus carrier from the LES + iter-035/049 transport + Step 4/5 affine input) is iter-053+.
